cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY 

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on robot grasping of deformable objects and proposes a novel grasp quality metric. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is also likely as the paper mentions using physical experiments to measure object deformability at different locations, which may involve computer vision techniques. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are possible categories as the paper may involve learning algorithms to optimize the grasp quality metric or to improve the grasp success rate. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also possible as the paper involves solving a linear program to compute the required work for a manipulation task, which may involve control theory.
